    <title>Supplementary data</title>
    <p id="p0355">The following are the Supplementary data to this article:<fig id="m0020" position="anchor"><label>Supplementary data 1</label><caption><p>The network is a 3D version of U-Net <xref rid="b0415" ref-type="bibr">[84]</xref> with 3D equivalents of operations (3D U-Net <xref rid="b0520" ref-type="bibr">[105]</xref>) with a reduced number of filters. The blue part is the encoder, which gradually reduces the image size using max-pooling, and the green part is the decoder part, which gradually increases the image size using transposed convolution. The input image is a 3D RGB image (here with labeled 53BP1 + γH2AX + DAPI) of size 96×96×48. The output has the same size, where eroded segmentation or detection images with Gaussians at IRIF positions are predicted for nucleus segmentation and IRIF detection, respectively.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="fx1"/></fig></p>
